JOHANNESBURG - Former Eskom CEO Matshela Koko is back at the state capture commission on Tuesday to testify about contracts signed with McKinsey. The commission said payments totalling R1.6 billion were made to McKinsey and Trillian. He will also testify about the Tegeta acquisition of Optimum Coal Mine and how Eskom allegedly enabled it by turning a R1.68 billion prepayment into a guarantee for the Gupta company. WATCH LIVE: Ex-Eskom CEO Matshela Koko returns to state capture inquiry  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.